WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:15.932 --> 00:00:19.561 position:50% align:center
[ELLIOT] To think that we could
be trounced so thoroughly.

00:00:19.644 --> 00:00:23.898 position:50% align:center
But then again,
that's Ike, I suppose.

00:00:23.982 --> 00:00:27.193 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] Isaac's like a child.
The only thing he cares about

00:00:27.277 --> 00:00:29.946 position:50% align:center
is strutting around
with his new toy.

00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:34.200 position:50% align:center
[ELLIOT] Hm! Has everyone
already been evacuated?

00:00:34.284 --> 00:00:37.412 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] It's underway.
Have a little patience.

00:00:48.340 --> 00:00:50.300 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT] Hey, there.
What's up, Elliot?

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:52.594 position:50% align:center
Hi, Karen.

00:00:52.677 --> 00:00:55.055 position:50% align:center
It's certainly been
a long time, Ike.

00:00:55.138 --> 00:00:57.432 position:50% align:center
If one were to judge by
your violent entrance,

00:00:57.515 --> 00:01:00.602 position:50% align:center
they might doubt that you
and I were ever old friends.

00:01:00.685 --> 00:01:01.728 position:50% align:center
It's funny, right?

00:01:01.811 --> 00:01:03.980 position:50% align:center
But don't worry,
I don't want too much.

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:07.192 position:50% align:center
I'm only here to bring
you and Karen back to DEM,

00:01:07.275 --> 00:01:09.986 position:50% align:center
where you both belong.

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.988 position:50% align:center
[ELLIOT]
Oh? And what if I refuse?

00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:16.534 position:50% align:center
Well, that's simple. Then you'll
just have to play with me.

00:01:16.618 --> 00:01:18.578 position:50% align:center
Beelzebub.

00:01:20.497 --> 00:01:23.375 position:50% align:center
All right, so be it.
How unfortunate for you.

00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:27.545 position:50% align:center
You've never been one
to listen to anyone else.

00:01:27.629 --> 00:01:29.547 position:50% align:center
Wait, Elliot, please don't.

00:01:29.631 --> 00:01:33.051 position:50% align:center
Everything will be fine, Karen.

00:01:33.134 --> 00:01:34.636 position:50% align:center
Now that I think of it,

00:01:34.719 --> 00:01:38.306 position:50% align:center
this is actually the first time
we've ever faced off, isn't it?

00:01:38.390 --> 00:01:41.976 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT] Yeah. I'm pretty
stressed out, as you can see.

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:45.980 position:50% align:center
Shaking in my boots at the
very thought. Shall we?

00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:55.532 position:50% align:center
â™ª

00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:30.877 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Mukuro.

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:33.004 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
So that's Mukuro?

00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:36.132 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:42.597 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Michael.

00:03:42.681 --> 00:03:44.182 position:50% align:center
Lataib.

00:03:54.776 --> 00:03:56.861 position:50% align:center
Deploy Protect Territory!

00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:05.370 position:50% align:center
Odd.

00:04:05.453 --> 00:04:06.579 position:50% align:center
Hey, check it out, Shido.

00:04:06.663 --> 00:04:08.998 position:50% align:center
You can get to your girl
without a spacesuit.

00:04:09.082 --> 00:04:11.334 position:50% align:center
You ready? It's do
or die time, now.

00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.378 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
I've got this. Send me to her.

00:04:13.461 --> 00:04:15.255 position:50% align:center
--[alarm]
--[ALL gasp]

00:04:15.338 --> 00:04:19.009 position:50% align:center
Not good, four DEM ships.

00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:20.677 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Goetia.

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:25.140 position:50% align:center
She sure got us good back before
history was changed, but now?

00:04:25.223 --> 00:04:28.226 position:50% align:center
I'm thrilled to see we're
gonna get a shot at revenge.

00:04:28.309 --> 00:04:32.063 position:50% align:center
Deploy Dual Territory:
Spatial Control and Defense!

00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.481 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Sir!

00:04:33.565 --> 00:04:36.317 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Time to teleport.
Mukuro's all yours, Shido.

00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:39.112 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] Leave it to me!
Stay safe, everybody!

00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:42.949 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:44.909 --> 00:04:47.412 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
You're Shido, is that correct?

00:04:47.495 --> 00:04:51.666 position:50% align:center
I already told you:
Muku doesn't want to be saved.

00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:53.793 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] The thing is,
I didn't actually come here

00:04:53.877 --> 00:04:57.047 position:50% align:center
to talk with you, though.
I'm here for the real Mukuro.

00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:59.174 position:50% align:center
The one whose
heart isn't locked.

00:04:59.257 --> 00:05:01.217 position:50% align:center
Seems pretty silly
since it was Muku

00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:03.136 position:50% align:center
who locked Muku's own heart.

00:05:03.219 --> 00:05:06.348 position:50% align:center
Have you ever considered minding
your own business, perhaps?

00:05:06.431 --> 00:05:10.143 position:50% align:center
Look. It doesn't make sense
to lock your own heart.

00:05:10.226 --> 00:05:11.686 position:50% align:center
So, what happened
that made you--?

00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:14.773 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO] You are, of course,
free to disregard my warning.

00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:17.150 position:50% align:center
Just as Muku is free to
deal with that rudeness

00:05:17.233 --> 00:05:19.736 position:50% align:center
in whatever way I
deem appropriate.

00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:23.698 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:25.992 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
As if I'd just hang out

00:05:26.076 --> 00:05:28.328 position:50% align:center
and let my big brother get hurt!

00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:29.704 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
You're the best, Kotori!

00:05:29.788 --> 00:05:31.289 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Duh.

00:05:31.373 --> 00:05:35.126 position:50% align:center
We're using Territory to detect
and dodge all incoming objects.

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:37.712 position:50% align:center
[MARIA] But be careful,
don't over-rely on it.

00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:40.465 position:50% align:center
You won't last getting
hit by an Angel.

00:05:40.548 --> 00:05:44.052 position:50% align:center
Got it! Thanks! Guys, you rock!

00:05:45.303 --> 00:05:47.555 position:50% align:center
Haniel!

00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:49.891 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Huh. Interesting.

00:05:49.974 --> 00:05:52.811 position:50% align:center
An Angel you stole from
a Spirit, I suppose?

00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:54.938 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Kinda harsh to say I stole it.

00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:59.609 position:50% align:center
I mean, come on, I'm borrowing
it to save you! Kaleidoscope!

00:06:03.321 --> 00:06:04.823 position:50% align:center
What's happening?

00:06:04.906 --> 00:06:08.284 position:50% align:center
 Mukuro, I'm gonna open
your heart with this!

00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.123 position:50% align:center
Commander,
it's the Bandersnatch.

00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:16.501 position:50% align:center
That's not all, either!
This response is...!

00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.380 position:50% align:center
Artemisia Ashcroft.

00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:21.464 position:50% align:center
Kotori!

00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:23.383 position:50% align:center
We're gonna get out
and fight, too.

00:06:23.466 --> 00:06:25.343 position:50% align:center
I'll help! Don't forget me!

00:06:25.427 --> 00:06:27.554 position:50% align:center
We'll make the wind blow like
nothing they've ever seen,

00:06:27.637 --> 00:06:29.389 position:50% align:center
even out here in
the airless sky!

00:06:29.472 --> 00:06:31.850 position:50% align:center
Concur. One thing we
won't do is sit around

00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:33.768 position:50% align:center
and do nothing
while this happens.

00:06:33.852 --> 00:06:36.104 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Hmm. Well, then, so be it.

00:06:36.187 --> 00:06:37.981 position:50% align:center
I was hoping to keep you
guys out of the fight

00:06:38.064 --> 00:06:40.525 position:50% align:center
for as long as possible, but...

00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50% align:center
MARIA, it's time for <i>that</i> .
Origami can handle it, for sure.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.239 position:50% align:center
[MARIA]
Roger.

00:06:47.866 --> 00:06:50.160 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
An emergency arming device/

00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:54.372 position:50% align:center
That's the
A-W-1-1-1, Brunhild.

00:06:54.456 --> 00:06:58.251 position:50% align:center
It's our latest model.
Put it to good use.

00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:07.927 position:50% align:center
[ALL grunt]

00:07:08.011 --> 00:07:10.930 position:50% align:center
That's a Territory hit!
No damage, though!

00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.016 position:50% align:center
Gosh, not even a
greeting first?

00:07:13.099 --> 00:07:15.185 position:50% align:center
Now that's a low blow, I'd say.

00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:18.313 position:50% align:center
There's a transmission.
Receiving.

00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:21.358 position:50% align:center
So we meet again,
Kotori Itsuka.

00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:23.401 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
What do you want, Ellen Mathers?

00:07:23.485 --> 00:07:26.946 position:50% align:center
Our surrender? Is that really
what you're holding out for?

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:28.406 position:50% align:center
Yes, that's correct.

00:07:28.490 --> 00:07:30.992 position:50% align:center
I see you have a new ship,
but it's useless.

00:07:31.076 --> 00:07:32.327 position:50% align:center
You have to know that.

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:35.038 position:50% align:center
I'll wreck it again
without hesitation.

00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:38.541 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Yeah, no doubt.
We can't be naÃ¯ve about that.

00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:40.794 position:50% align:center
And there's no way they're
unaware that in the other world,

00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:43.630 position:50% align:center
Fraxinus was
destroyed by Goetia.

00:07:45.048 --> 00:07:47.926 position:50% align:center
Beelzebub's power
is impressive, indeed.

00:07:48.009 --> 00:07:49.386 position:50% align:center
How nice for you.

00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.471 position:50% align:center
The boss must be in a good mood.

00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:53.807 position:50% align:center
Good instincts. It's true.

00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:56.851 position:50% align:center
His spirits have been
uncharacteristically high.

00:07:56.935 --> 00:07:59.062 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Well, yeah,
that's pretty obvious.

00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:01.564 position:50% align:center
Otherwise, he wouldn't be out
here invading enemy bases

00:08:01.648 --> 00:08:02.649 position:50% align:center
by himself.

00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:05.318 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN gasps]
Wait, what did you say?

00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:07.529 position:50% align:center
Ike attacked Ratatoskr?

00:08:07.612 --> 00:08:10.365 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Oh wow, you mean
you didn't know? Weird!

00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:12.492 position:50% align:center
Here I was thinking you
two were super tight,

00:08:12.575 --> 00:08:14.661 position:50% align:center
but I guess he doesn't
actually trust you.

00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:16.121 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN gasps]

00:08:16.204 --> 00:08:19.124 position:50% align:center
If you think I'm lying,
go check it out for yourself.

00:08:19.207 --> 00:08:22.002 position:50% align:center
Or are you scared
to know the truth?

00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:24.963 position:50% align:center
Trying to rile me won't work.
Save your breath.

00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:28.383 position:50% align:center
I'll just plan to look into it
once this battle is over.

00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:31.261 position:50% align:center
It won't take me more
than five minutes.

00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:37.434 position:50% align:center
[SHIIZAKI] Enemy is on
the move to surround.

00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:39.144 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Okay, change of plans:

00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:42.647 position:50% align:center
only Tohka and Origami go out.
Everyone else, standby.

00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:44.649 position:50% align:center
Aww! Why? I wanna go, too!

00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:47.652 position:50% align:center
Opinion. We can provide
help in the way of backup.

00:08:47.736 --> 00:08:49.612 position:50% align:center
Don't sweat it, guys.
I've got a plan.

00:08:49.696 --> 00:08:52.991 position:50% align:center
So for now, please just
do as I say.

00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:56.202 position:50% align:center
Go ahead. Bring it on,
dear rival o' mine.

00:08:56.286 --> 00:09:00.040 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna show you the
power of the new Fraxinus.

00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:03.960 position:50% align:center
Now, shall we begin our
little date with destiny?

00:09:07.756 --> 00:09:09.257 position:50% align:center
Lataib.

00:09:11.634 --> 00:09:13.094 position:50% align:center
Zadkiel!

00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:17.640 position:50% align:center
How strange. Are you positive
that you're truly human?

00:09:17.724 --> 00:09:20.727 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah, that's what I like
to tell myself, at least!

00:09:24.814 --> 00:09:27.025 position:50% align:center
And now, Artemisia Ashcroft?

00:09:27.108 --> 00:09:31.571 position:50% align:center
Apologies, but I'm afraid
I'll be taking that Spirit!

00:09:33.948 --> 00:09:36.576 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA, SHIDO gasp]

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:41.748 position:50% align:center
Shido, you good?

00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:43.583 position:50% align:center
Origami?!

00:09:43.667 --> 00:09:44.876 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:09:47.545 --> 00:09:49.589 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
Shido!

00:09:49.673 --> 00:09:50.882 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.260 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Hm.

00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.054 position:50% align:center
Are you doing okay, Shido?

00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:58.640 position:50% align:center
All good! Can't thank
you enough, Tohka!

00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:00.850 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:02.560 position:50% align:center
Zadkiel! Go!

00:10:05.480 --> 00:10:07.232 position:50% align:center
Sandalphon!

00:10:10.985 --> 00:10:12.946 position:50% align:center
Fall back, Tohka! Go on!

00:10:13.029 --> 00:10:13.822 position:50% align:center
Are you sure?

00:10:13.905 --> 00:10:15.156 position:50% align:center
I'll be fine.

00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:17.742 position:50% align:center
Hey, Kotori, little favor?

00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:25.542 position:50% align:center
Artemisia, why would you
choose to be with DEM?

00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:26.793 position:50% align:center
I don't get it.

00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:28.169 position:50% align:center
It doesn't make sense
to me that you would be

00:10:28.253 --> 00:10:29.713 position:50% align:center
so friendly with them.

00:10:29.796 --> 00:10:32.257 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA gasps]

00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:35.593 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA] Explain to me
how it is you know my name?

00:10:35.677 --> 00:10:39.180 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA grunts]

00:10:39.264 --> 00:10:42.183 position:50% align:center
It doesn't matter. As long
as you're in the way,

00:10:42.267 --> 00:10:44.769 position:50% align:center
it seems that I can't
complete my mission.

00:10:44.853 --> 00:10:48.064 position:50% align:center
Sorry, but I'll have
to destroy you now!

00:10:48.148 --> 00:10:49.691 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI grunts]

00:10:51.443 --> 00:10:54.946 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI] You're strong.
Way stronger than me.

00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:57.115 position:50% align:center
I mean, as a Wizard.

00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:58.616 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:02.245 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA]
Wait, are you?

00:11:02.328 --> 00:11:05.415 position:50% align:center
Of course. Now I see.

00:11:05.498 --> 00:11:08.209 position:50% align:center
You were there when
I came for Sister.

00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:11.629 position:50% align:center
How fortunate.

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:15.133 position:50% align:center
If you're a Spirit, then I
can kill you guilt-free.

00:11:24.726 --> 00:11:27.937 position:50% align:center
Yggdrafolium! Deploy one
through ten immediately!

00:11:43.578 --> 00:11:46.956 position:50% align:center
Converging cannon, Mistilteinn!
And, fire!

00:12:04.099 --> 00:12:06.559 position:50% align:center
That's one of Fraxinus'
new powers.

00:12:06.643 --> 00:12:09.771 position:50% align:center
Modeled off Goetia,
I'm extremely sorry to say.

00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:12.399 position:50% align:center
There is no denying that your
power and maneuverability

00:12:12.482 --> 00:12:14.234 position:50% align:center
have greatly increased.

00:12:14.317 --> 00:12:17.362 position:50% align:center
However, it's just as certain
that those who challenge Heaven

00:12:17.445 --> 00:12:19.906 position:50% align:center
will have their wings plucked.

00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:22.867 position:50% align:center
For they shall be scorched
by the flames of God.

00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:38.591 position:50% align:center
[gasps, grunts]

00:12:41.177 --> 00:12:45.140 position:50% align:center
I mean, come on, who said we
could only have one trump card?

00:12:45.223 --> 00:12:46.558 position:50% align:center
Thanks, you guys.

00:12:46.641 --> 00:12:49.394 position:50% align:center
There's no way my Spirit power
alone would've cut it.

00:12:49.477 --> 00:12:52.105 position:50% align:center
Sure! I'm glad to get
the chance to help out.

00:12:52.188 --> 00:12:54.149 position:50% align:center
Same! 'Cause when we
all come together,

00:12:54.232 --> 00:12:56.234 position:50% align:center
it's like we're
totally unbeatable!

00:12:56.317 --> 00:12:57.819 position:50% align:center
This feels amazing!

00:12:57.902 --> 00:13:00.488 position:50% align:center
It's as if all our Spirit powers
are getting mixed up together!

00:13:00.572 --> 00:13:02.157 position:50% align:center
Something about that
makes me happier

00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:04.367 position:50% align:center
than I ever could've imagined!

00:13:04.451 --> 00:13:05.910 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
System Blot:

00:13:05.994 --> 00:13:09.748 position:50% align:center
a new weapon, which is driven
completely by Spirit power.

00:13:09.831 --> 00:13:13.084 position:50% align:center
It will surpass even
the limits of Territory.

00:13:13.168 --> 00:13:15.920 position:50% align:center
This time, victory is ours.
I'm certain of it!

00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:18.757 position:50% align:center
Bite the dust,
World's Strongest Wizard!

00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:25.221 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:29.726 position:50% align:center
Awesome. That's all
we have left.

00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:32.145 position:50% align:center
Let's get in there
and clean 'em up!

00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:36.816 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:38.735 position:50% align:center
You're really still here?

00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:41.279 position:50% align:center
Not a very fast learner,
are you, Shido?

00:13:41.363 --> 00:13:43.656 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Hm! I told you.

00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:46.785 position:50% align:center
I came to unlock to your heart,
so that's what I'll do!

00:13:46.868 --> 00:13:48.244 position:50% align:center
Now, Michael!

00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:54.501 position:50% align:center
Let's go, Tohka!

00:13:54.584 --> 00:13:55.502 position:50% align:center
Right!

00:13:55.585 --> 00:13:57.712 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA shouts]

00:13:57.796 --> 00:13:59.005 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:00.382 --> 00:14:03.968 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO] Hmm. I had a
feeling you'd try that.

00:14:04.052 --> 00:14:08.473 position:50% align:center
A worthy attempt, but now,
it's all over for you.

00:14:09.974 --> 00:14:12.018 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Quick, do it now, Shido!

00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:14.187 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:17.816 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO] Are you kidding?
Just who are you?

00:14:17.899 --> 00:14:20.652 position:50% align:center
Just your friendly,
neighborhood high schooler.

00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:22.237 position:50% align:center
Lataib!

00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:27.200 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:28.952 --> 00:14:30.286 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
Metatron!

00:14:32.747 --> 00:14:37.752 position:50% align:center
Not bad. Combining Spirit
power and generative magic.

00:14:37.836 --> 00:14:40.130 position:50% align:center
Huh? Goetia!

00:14:41.548 --> 00:14:43.967 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
You've lost. Give up the fight.

00:14:47.721 --> 00:14:49.556 position:50% align:center
[ARTEMISIA]
No, I'm afraid you're wrong.

00:14:49.639 --> 00:14:54.019 position:50% align:center
Because, you see, our goal is
to take out all these Spirits!

00:14:56.396 --> 00:14:57.605 position:50% align:center
Shido!

00:14:58.690 --> 00:14:59.774 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:59.858 --> 00:15:02.652 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Mukuro! Zadkiel, now!

00:15:04.821 --> 00:15:06.656 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA, NATSUMI, ORIGAMI]
Shido!

00:15:14.456 --> 00:15:18.335 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] It's all right, Mukuro!
I've got you. You're okay!

00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:20.045 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO gasps]

00:15:33.767 --> 00:15:35.393 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO'S MOTHER]
It's so nice to meet you.

00:15:35.477 --> 00:15:37.103 position:50% align:center
I'm going to be your
mother from now on.

00:15:37.187 --> 00:15:39.064 position:50% align:center
And this place is going
to be your new home.

00:15:39.147 --> 00:15:40.940 position:50% align:center
And this is your father.

00:15:41.024 --> 00:15:43.068 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO'S FATHER]
It's great to meet you.

00:15:43.151 --> 00:15:47.238 position:50% align:center
 I'm gonna be your sister,
so let's be friends, huh?

00:15:49.491 --> 00:15:50.867 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Mm-hm.

00:16:03.046 --> 00:16:04.172 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:04.255 --> 00:16:05.382 position:50% align:center
--[KOTORI] There he is.
--[YOSHINO] He's okay!

00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:07.300 position:50% align:center
--[YUZURU] Boy!
--[MIKU] My darling!

00:16:07.384 --> 00:16:08.677 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
Is something wrong, Shido?

00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:10.345 position:50% align:center
Looks like you're crying.

00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:14.099 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO grunts] Don't worry, it's
just from a weird dream I had.

00:16:14.182 --> 00:16:15.558 position:50% align:center
Where is this?

00:16:15.642 --> 00:16:17.519 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Fraxinus' infirmary.

00:16:17.602 --> 00:16:21.439 position:50% align:center
It wasn't easy catching you out
of the sky, I'll have you know.

00:16:21.523 --> 00:16:22.899 position:50% align:center
Oh, that's right.

00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:25.568 position:50% align:center
And Mukuro? What about Mukuro?

00:16:25.652 --> 00:16:27.278 position:50% align:center
Sadly, we don't know.

00:16:27.362 --> 00:16:30.573 position:50% align:center
During the fall, the two of
you got separated, so...

00:16:30.657 --> 00:16:32.200 position:50% align:center
For real? Then what--?

00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:34.577 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Muku is right here, Shido.

00:16:34.661 --> 00:16:35.995 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:16:36.079 --> 00:16:37.247 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Mukuro?

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:39.916 position:50% align:center
What a mean guy, making
poor Muku wait so long.

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:41.418 position:50% align:center
But, everything's fine.

00:16:41.501 --> 00:16:44.212 position:50% align:center
In fact, I think I'm in the best
mood I've ever been in.

00:16:44.295 --> 00:16:45.714 position:50% align:center
Oh. Uh. Are you...?

00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:48.216 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO giggles]
Such a sourpuss.

00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:49.592 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Uh...

00:16:49.676 --> 00:16:51.344 position:50% align:center
Huh? What's going on?

00:16:51.428 --> 00:16:53.555 position:50% align:center
Is this because your
heart has opened up?

00:16:53.638 --> 00:16:55.098 position:50% align:center
That's a fact.

00:16:55.181 --> 00:16:57.600 position:50% align:center
It looks as though her full
scale of emotions has returned.

00:16:57.684 --> 00:17:00.687 position:50% align:center
Right, yeah, but even
if that's true...

00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:03.732 position:50% align:center
Mukuro, it's as if you're an
entirely different person.

00:17:03.815 --> 00:17:06.026 position:50% align:center
Is it so very hard to
believe that Muku's heart

00:17:06.109 --> 00:17:08.653 position:50% align:center
might've actually been touched
by the one who put his own life

00:17:08.737 --> 00:17:10.488 position:50% align:center
at risk to open it for her?

00:17:10.572 --> 00:17:13.658 position:50% align:center
I don't see why
anyone would doubt it.

00:17:13.742 --> 00:17:16.161 position:50% align:center
The moment when it was
finally unlocked,

00:17:16.244 --> 00:17:18.955 position:50% align:center
I was nearly overwhelmed
with all the big feelings.

00:17:19.039 --> 00:17:21.666 position:50% align:center
Most of which was
gratitude for you.

00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:26.212 position:50% align:center
Although, I'm sure there must be
other reasons I'm fond of you.

00:17:26.296 --> 00:17:28.673 position:50% align:center
Let me see.

00:17:28.757 --> 00:17:30.800 position:50% align:center
Uh, well, just because.
That's all.

00:17:30.884 --> 00:17:32.385 position:50% align:center
Aw, come on.

00:17:32.469 --> 00:17:35.347 position:50% align:center
Truth. I like you just because.

00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:39.309 position:50% align:center
I kinda feel like you and Muku
are already close, somehow.

00:17:39.392 --> 00:17:40.894 position:50% align:center
Oh, you do?

00:17:40.977 --> 00:17:45.690 position:50% align:center
Anyway, since it looks as though
you haven't quite recovered yet,

00:17:45.774 --> 00:17:49.027 position:50% align:center
I shall leave you and
come visit you tomorrow.

00:17:49.110 --> 00:17:52.489 position:50% align:center
So until we meet again,
bye, mister.

00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:58.078 position:50% align:center
Didn't see that one coming!
I can't believe that was Mukuro.

00:17:58.161 --> 00:18:00.705 position:50% align:center
I gotta say, her personality
is nothing like

00:18:00.789 --> 00:18:01.915 position:50% align:center
what I'd heard before!

00:18:01.998 --> 00:18:03.458 position:50% align:center
Astonishment.

00:18:03.541 --> 00:18:06.795 position:50% align:center
I had consistently imagined
her to be a very rude Spirit.

00:18:06.878 --> 00:18:09.255 position:50% align:center
But oh gosh, what a cutie,
don't you think?

00:18:09.339 --> 00:18:11.800 position:50% align:center
She's got that tiny frame,
but with nice little spots

00:18:11.883 --> 00:18:13.718 position:50% align:center
of fluffiness right
where it counts.

00:18:13.802 --> 00:18:17.430 position:50% align:center
He, he, he. Darling is
such a total perv!

00:18:17.514 --> 00:18:18.807 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO grunts]

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:21.142 position:50% align:center
She said she'll be
coming back tomorrow.

00:18:21.226 --> 00:18:23.311 position:50% align:center
But what then, Shido?

00:18:23.395 --> 00:18:24.813 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's a good question.

00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:27.816 position:50% align:center
All right, enough!
We'll discuss that stuff later.

00:18:27.899 --> 00:18:31.444 position:50% align:center
Shido's still healing up,
so we shouldn't tire him out.

00:18:31.528 --> 00:18:34.447 position:50% align:center
The ship does have some
brand-new facilities, you know.

00:18:34.531 --> 00:18:37.742 position:50% align:center
Why not check 'em out and just
focus on soothing your body?

00:18:37.826 --> 00:18:39.202 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
What "new facilities"?

00:18:39.285 --> 00:18:40.704 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI giggles]

00:18:44.165 --> 00:18:49.295 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO sighs] So, it's a bath
imbued with magic, huh?

00:18:49.379 --> 00:18:52.549 position:50% align:center
It guess it must be true,
'cause I really do feel great!

00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:57.762 position:50% align:center
Oh, right. I wonder what that
weird dream was all about?

00:18:57.846 --> 00:19:00.098 position:50% align:center
That little girl, she was...

00:19:03.309 --> 00:19:06.396 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO yells]

00:19:06.479 --> 00:19:08.148 position:50% align:center
Something's just occurred to me.

00:19:08.231 --> 00:19:10.442 position:50% align:center
It's hard to wash
while you're injured.

00:19:10.525 --> 00:19:11.943 position:50% align:center
I'll help, sound good?

00:19:12.027 --> 00:19:14.112 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] Whoa, whoa!
Thanks, I'll be fine!

00:19:14.195 --> 00:19:17.866 position:50% align:center
Just leave it to me.
I'm gonna lick you clean.

00:19:17.949 --> 00:19:19.367 position:50% align:center
I mean... wash.

00:19:19.451 --> 00:19:21.244 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] You definitely
just said, "lick"!

00:19:21.327 --> 00:19:23.663 position:50% align:center
[ALL cheer, laugh]

00:19:23.747 --> 00:19:25.040 position:50% align:center
Hello, my darling!

00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:27.876 position:50% align:center
I've come here to wash your
back and whatever else!

00:19:27.959 --> 00:19:29.127 position:50% align:center
Shido! How are you?

00:19:29.210 --> 00:19:31.629 position:50% align:center
Still the same?
I'm here to help, okay?

00:19:31.713 --> 00:19:33.757 position:50% align:center
I'm so happy to find you
in the healing bath.

00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:34.966 position:50% align:center
Isn't it just great?

00:19:35.050 --> 00:19:37.302 position:50% align:center
Reminisce. When it comes
to bathing together,

00:19:37.385 --> 00:19:39.637 position:50% align:center
you're gonna want the
Yamai Sisters every time.

00:19:39.721 --> 00:19:41.056 position:50% align:center
That's for sure.

00:19:41.139 --> 00:19:44.392 position:50% align:center
Hey, everyone. Keep in mind
Shido came here to heal,

00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:46.519 position:50% align:center
so let's not forget
that, all right?

00:19:46.603 --> 00:19:48.021 position:50% align:center
Yes, it's clear.

00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:50.482 position:50% align:center
Not all of us were needed to
assist Shido with his bath.

00:19:50.565 --> 00:19:52.192 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINO giggles]
It's true.

00:19:52.275 --> 00:19:55.403 position:50% align:center
But bathing together with
everyone still sounds fun to me!

00:19:55.487 --> 00:19:58.239 position:50% align:center
I just had a brilliant idea!
How 'bout if you and Yoshino

00:19:58.323 --> 00:19:59.699 position:50% align:center
take turns washing
each other's backs?

00:19:59.783 --> 00:20:02.035 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI gasps]
You're serious, though?

00:20:02.118 --> 00:20:02.994 position:50% align:center
You wouldn't mind?

00:20:03.078 --> 00:20:04.954 position:50% align:center
Ah! Let me tell you.

00:20:05.038 --> 00:20:07.415 position:50% align:center
These cuties make for
such a killer view!

00:20:07.499 --> 00:20:08.458 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:12.754 position:50% align:center
[ALL laughing, shouting]

00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:15.423 position:50% align:center
Look at you!

00:20:15.507 --> 00:20:18.551 position:50% align:center
Yes, we may have shaken hands
a little bit too hard.

00:20:18.635 --> 00:20:21.346 position:50% align:center
I guess Elliot was excited
to see me, though.

00:20:21.429 --> 00:20:23.556 position:50% align:center
Why wouldn't anyone be,
you know?

00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:25.934 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN] So, what you're
saying is, it's the truth?

00:20:26.017 --> 00:20:29.437 position:50% align:center
You attacked Ratatoskr's base
without telling me a thing?

00:20:29.521 --> 00:20:31.481 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Unfortunately, though,

00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:35.110 position:50% align:center
I seem to have allowed Elliot
to slip right out of my reach.

00:20:35.193 --> 00:20:38.196 position:50% align:center
Oh, and your little sister, too.

00:20:38.279 --> 00:20:39.989 position:50% align:center
Still, with Realizers,

00:20:40.073 --> 00:20:43.201 position:50% align:center
I should be back up
on my feet tomorrow.

00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:45.495 position:50% align:center
You didn't fare so
well yourself, either,

00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:47.038 position:50% align:center
did you, Ellen?

00:20:47.122 --> 00:20:49.958 position:50% align:center
I accept that due to my own
shortcomings, I fully deserve

00:20:50.041 --> 00:20:53.169 position:50% align:center
whatever punishment there
might be in store for me.

00:20:53.253 --> 00:20:57.048 position:50% align:center
But, listen, Ike, I really do
think you owe me an explanation.

00:20:57.132 --> 00:21:00.343 position:50% align:center
How could you not have
told me that about Elliot?

00:21:00.427 --> 00:21:03.722 position:50% align:center
Tell me this. If I'd brought
you, isn't it safe to assume

00:21:03.805 --> 00:21:06.182 position:50% align:center
you would've killed
Elliot without question?

00:21:06.266 --> 00:21:07.475 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:13.815 --> 00:21:15.191 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Ready to go, Shido?

00:21:15.275 --> 00:21:19.112 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but where're we going?
Where am I meeting Mukuro?

00:21:19.195 --> 00:21:21.448 position:50% align:center
Am I heading back to space?

00:21:21.531 --> 00:21:23.533 position:50% align:center
That's the big question,
isn't it?

00:21:23.616 --> 00:21:25.869 position:50% align:center
I mean, she said she'd come
back so we feel pretty certain

00:21:25.952 --> 00:21:28.079 position:50% align:center
that she will, but still...

00:21:28.163 --> 00:21:29.205 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI gasps]

00:21:29.289 --> 00:21:31.624 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO]
Hello. It's time, Mister.

00:21:31.708 --> 00:21:34.169 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps, shouts]

00:21:34.252 --> 00:21:35.587 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Shido!

00:21:41.343 --> 00:21:43.178 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:21:47.349 --> 00:21:49.476 position:50% align:center
You see? Here we are
on the surface,

00:21:49.559 --> 00:21:52.020 position:50% align:center
just exactly like
you wanted, right?

00:21:52.103 --> 00:21:54.522 position:50% align:center
Do you remember? You said
there were lots of fun things

00:21:54.606 --> 00:21:57.275 position:50% align:center
for people to do down here!

00:21:57.359 --> 00:22:00.528 position:50% align:center
So! Let's get going,
shall we, mister?

00:22:05.450 --> 00:22:10.455 position:50% align:center line:10%
